<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="16" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
<pageBreakToken pageId="15" pageNumber="16" start="start">Description</pageBreakToken>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
Basidiocarps resupinate, yellow, fragile, pores shallow and large (1-4 per mm). Hyphal structure monomitic, simple-septate, loose, hyphae not swollen, wider (4-5 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
in diameter) in subiculum, a bit narrower in trama (3-4 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
). Hymenial branching corymb-like, subulate thin-walled cystidia present. Spores rather large (6
<normalizedToken originalValue="–7×">-7x</normalizedToken>
3 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
), cylindrical to narrowly ellipsoid.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="16" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
This monotypic genus comes close to 
<taxonomicName class="Agaricomycetes" family="Polyporaceae" genus="Riopa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Riopa" order="Polyporales" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="genus">Riopa</taxonomicName>
both morphologically and phylogenetically, though the two do not seem to form a monophyletic group (Figure 2). Morphological differences are summarized in Table 2.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
